snippet.title: The Story of Creator Camp | 5 Friends, 1 Dream, and a Plan to change the internet forever.
snippet.description:
Thank you to Notion for bringing this project and business to life.
Learn more about their new Q&A feature here (it's really cool): http://tiny.cc/np2gvz

No pressure, but If you also click this link, I'll probably be able to make more videos like these, haha: https://ntn.so/maxreisinger1 !! 🙂

Notion isn't just for businesses, you can also use it for your personal life, school, etc! Here's a video from my friend Jade about how she organizes her Notion: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=67jFfjwUvRQ&ab_channel=UnJadedJade)

Want to help build Creator Camp with us? Apply here: https://3v5hj3r57d3.typeform.com/creatorcamp

Over the next few weeks, we’re opening up 3-month internships for a variety of roles. We’re tinkering on a few special projects, building out our YouTube channel/newsletter, and working with many incredible brands & creators. If you’re at all remotely interested in what we’re up to, I highly recommend applying. For any questions, please reach out to contact@creatorcamp.co -- (once your app is submitted, we’ll send more details). 

Learn more about @creatorcamp. : https://creatorcamp.co/
The internet makes us more connected than ever before in history, yet people feel lonelier than they ever have been. We're on a mission to make the internet a better place. By bringing together the next generation of creators, storytellers, filmmakers, musicians, artists, and entrepreneurs, we believe that real change can be made. Call us crazy internet optimists if you like, but we believe in a better future, one that starts today. 

Watch my Tedx talk on how I believe we can use social media for good: https://www.ted.com/talks/max_reisinger_stop_trying_to_quit_social_media

A huge thank you to Elliot Bisnow for helping bring our dreams to life. We would not even be close to where we are today without your guidance and inspiration. Thank you, Elliot! The book "The Third Door" first introduced me to Elliot & all the incredible things he's done. He's also the author of an incredible book that recently came out. Read it here: http://tiny.cc/1n2gvz -- You can also dive deep here with an incredible 2+ hour podcast: http://tiny.cc/vn2gvz

Co-produced and co-dreamed by @officialsebvon  (one of the most talented people I know, if not the most)

Montana + Camp 1.0 videos from @wholesomesimon & @RyanNgFilms 

Additional footage by @chrwaited 

Music by friend Bartholomew! @mandelbro1  (Spotify: https://tinyurl.com/57xswz6)
--

snippet.title: A Random French Kid Asked Me to Hang Out..
snippet.description:
I got a dm on Instagram from a French kid asking me to hang out for the day... We met up and this is what happened:

Here's a quote that I believe sums up this awesome day:

"Find a way to say yes to things. Say yes to invitations to a new country, say yes to meet new friends, say yes to learning a new language, picking up a new sport. Yes is how you get your first job, and your next job, and your spouse, and even your kids. Even if it's a bit edgy, a bit out of your comfort zone, saying yes means that you will do something new, meet someone new, and make a difference in your life. Yes lets you stand out in a crowd, be the optimist, to stay positive, be the one everyone comes to. Yes is what keeps us all young." 
-Eric Schmidt

Go make someone smile, go for an adventure, go try something new!
Let me know how it goes! Send me a dm, I'd love to hear about it (:

https://www.instagram.com/maxbrsee/?h...

snippet.title: Is This The Most Beautiful Beach In France..??
snippet.description:
You don't want to miss out on these incredible drone shots...

In this video, we hiked to one of the many beautiful calanques in the Marseille/Cassis area. Here's some more information:

"Calanques are essentially inlets that are formed by glaciers. Many times, they are partially submerged in the ocean and are formed out of limestone. These geologic formations are notable for typically having steep sides. The calanques in Marseille and Cassis are the most famous examples of these kinds of beautiful formations, which can also be considered fjords of the Mediterranean variety. Visitors of Marseille will not only be able to enjoy the beaches, deltas, and charming coastal towns, but also the miles of rugged calanques that stretch between Marseille and Cassis. Climbing calanques in Provence France has long been a favorite pastime of residents and tourists alike. The magnificent natural creations stretch for over sixteen miles between Marseille and Cassis and are over two and a half miles wide. You can explore the enchanting Calanques from a variety of points, and hiking is available year round except for in July and August when there is an increased chance of fire from the heat."

Credit: http://www.destination360.com/europe/france/marseille/calanques

Go make someone smile, go for an adventure, go try something new!
Let me know how it goes! Send me a dm, I'd love to hear about it (:

"Calanques are essentially inlets that are formed by glaciers. Many times, they are partially submerged in the ocean and are formed out of limestone. These geologic formations are notable for typically having steep sides. The calanques in Marseille and Cassis are the most famous examples of these kinds of beautiful formations, which can also be considered fjords of the Mediterranean variety. Visitors of Marseille will not only be able to enjoy the beaches, deltas, and charming coastal towns, but also the miles of rugged calanques that stretch between Marseille and Cassis. Climbing calanques in Provence France has long been a favorite pastime of residents and tourists alike. The magnificent natural creations stretch for over sixteen miles between Marseille and Cassis and are over two and a half miles wide. You can explore the enchanting Calanques from a variety of points, and hiking is available year round except for in July and August when there is an increased chance of fire from the heat."

Credit: http://www.destination360.com/europe/france/marseille/calanques

Go make someone smile, go for an adventure, go try something new!

WHO AM I? ♻️
Hello! My name is Max Reisinger (Rye - Singer) and I’m a 17-year old student-athlete/entrepreneur/visual creative. I’m currently in my last year in high school and am applying to college/university (wish me luck). I’ve been creating videos here on YouTube since the beginning of 2019 when I moved to France for 7 months with my family. I attended a French public school during my time there and filmed all of my experiences/travels/new perspectives. After moving back to America, I started a business (https://perspectopia.com) and have continued to film how I use optimism to live a happy, well-balanced life. 

MY BUSINESS: 📦 (https://instagram.com/perspectopia - https://perspectopia.com)
At the beginning of 2020, I started a clothing brand - Perspectopia (Perspective + Utopia). My ultimate goal with this YouTube channel has always been to create a community and I strongly believe that optimistic perspectives can change your life. So, I decided to create a community based upon these ideas and also decided to create a line of clothing so that you can represent these same ideals. 

The first collection launched at the beginning of 2020 where I released a limited round of 100 embroidered champion hoodies. You guys absolutely blew me away and they sold out in less than 9 minutes!!? If you want to support the Perspectopia movement and rep the brand, follow @persptopia on Instagram (https://instagram.com/perspectopia) to get updates on all future drops, updates, and behind the scenes!

snippet.title: A Random French Kid Asked Me to Hang Out..
snippet.description:
I got a dm on Instagram from a French kid asking me to hang out for the day... We met up and this is what happened:

Here's a quote that I believe sums up this awesome day:

"Find a way to say yes to things. Say yes to invitations to a new country, say yes to meet new friends, say yes to learning a new language, picking up a new sport. Yes is how you get your first job, and your next job, and your spouse, and even your kids. Even if it's a bit edgy, a bit out of your comfort zone, saying yes means that you will do something new, meet someone new, and make a difference in your life. Yes lets you stand out in a crowd, be the optimist, to stay positive, be the one everyone comes to. Yes is what keeps us all young." 
-Eric Schmidt

Go make someone smile, go for an adventure, go try something new!
Let me know how it goes! Send me a dm, I'd love to hear about it (:

snippet.title: my productive after school night routine (even tho i'm usually so tired)
snippet.description:
hi guys!!
todays video i show you my after school/ night routine! i have school 3 days a week but only go up to campus twice! i usually am so tired after school but still want to be productive and get things done! today i got boba, worked on homework, went to the gym, made pasta, watched a show and chilled, cleansed my crystals, edited a video and showed you my shower routine! thank u guys so much for watching and i’ll see u in my next video :)

snippet.title: Don't Toss That Nutella Jar! Make INSANE Nutella Ice Cream in MINUTES! (2-Ingredient Hack!)
snippet.description:
Craving Nutella but the jar's looking lonely?  Don't toss it! Give it a delicious makeover with this EASY 2-ingredient Nutella ice cream hack that's gone viral on TikTok!

All you need is:

An almost-empty Nutella jar (with a little Nutella goodness clinging to the sides)
Heavy whipping cream
Here's the magic:

Pour in enough heavy cream to fill the jar almost to the top.
Shake, shake, SHAKE! ️ The Nutella should swirl into the cream, creating a dreamy Nutella-infused base.
Pop it in the freezer for at least 2 hours (or overnight for the ultimate scoopability).
Voila! Instant Nutella ice cream heaven!
Bonus tips:

Add a pinch of salt for an extra flavor pop.
Swirl in some chopped hazelnuts or chocolate chips for extra texture.
Top with a drizzle of Nutella before serving for the ultimate Nutella overload.
Get ready to amaze your taste buds with this simple and satisfying hack! Share your Nutella ice cream creations with us in the comments below!

#nutella #icecream #dessert #easyrecipes #tiktokhacks #foodhacks #chocolatelover #homemade #treatyourself
